Available naming cases
1) CamelCase (Capitalize all words whiout spaces, Underscore)
2) pascal Case (Capitalize 2nd word forward, whiout spaces, Underscore)
3) Snake _ Case (use small letters, separate all words by _ underscore)


We are going to use snake_care 
Language (English)
Void reserved words : Don't use SQL, Python , C# , VBA reserved words as object names

---

Bronze Rules

All names must start with the source system name, and table name match their original names without renamming.
<entity> : Extract table name from the source system.
crm_customer_info --> customer information from the CRM system.


Silver Rules

All names must start with the source system name, and table name match their original names without renamming.
<entity> : Extract table name from the source system.
crm_customer_info --> customer information from the CRM system.



Gold Rules

All names must startuse meaningful, business-aligned names for tables, starting with the catefory prefix.
<category> : Descripe the role of the table, such as dim (dimension) or fact (fact table).
<entity> : Descriptive name of the table, aligned with the business domain  (e.g., customers, product, Sales).
Examples:
   dim_Customers --> Dimension table for customer data.
fact_sales --> Fact table containing sales transactions.

Glossary of category patterns

Pattern    Meaning                           Example
dim_       Dimention table                  dim_customer , dim_product
fact_      Fact table                       fact_sales
agg_       Aggregated table                 agg_Customers ,  agg_Sales_monthly




